        <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4 mb-4"><h3 class="text-sm font-bold mb-2">Do corporate cafeterias in Plano need kitchen fire suppression systems?</h3><p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Yes. Corporate cafeterias producing grease-laden vapors from commercial cooking equipment are subject to the same NFPA 96 requirements as public restaurants — automatic wet chemical suppression, semi-annual inspection, Class K extinguisher within 30 feet of cooking surfaces, and hood cleaning at required intervals. Plano's large corporate campus population makes this one of the most frequently missed compliance obligations in the city.</p></div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-3 mt-8">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
        <div class="flex flex-col gap-4 mb-8"><div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4"><h3 class="text-sm font-bold mb-2">Does every Plano restaurant need a kitchen fire suppression system?</h3><p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Yes. All commercial cooking operations in Plano producing grease-laden vapors must have an automatic wet chemical suppression system under NFPA 96 and the International Fire Code (IFC). This applies to restaurants, bars with food service, hotel kitchens, and corporate cafeterias.</p></div><div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4"><h3 class="text-sm font-bold mb-2">How often does kitchen fire suppression need to be inspected in Plano?</h3><p class="text-sm text-gray-600">NFPA 96 requires semi-annual inspection — twice per year — for all commercial kitchen suppression systems. Inspection must be performed by a licensed contractor and documented. The Plano Fire-Rescue enforces this requirement.</p></div><div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4"><h3 class="text-sm font-bold mb-2">How much does kitchen suppression inspection cost in Plano?</h3><p class="text-sm text-gray-600">$175–$350 per system per system. Budget for two inspections annually.</p></div><div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4"><h3 class="text-sm font-bold mb-2">What is the most common kitchen fire safety violation in Plano?</h3><p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Common violations in Plano include: Overdue semi-annual kitchen suppression inspection in Legacy West food hall tenant spaces — high turnover creates compliance gaps; Corporate cafeteria suppression not on semi-annual schedule — campus facility managers overlook NFPA 96 as a separate obligation.</p></div><div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4"><h3 class="text-sm font-bold mb-2">Who licenses kitchen suppression contractors in TX?</h3><p class="text-sm text-gray-600">The Texas State Fire Marshal's Office ((512) 676-6000) licenses fire protection contractors statewide. Verify your suppression contractor holds current TX credentials before scheduling service.</p></div></div>
